23429	23429	small apples, crabapple. Small apple-like fruits, often referring to aratilis or small local fruits.	小リンゴ・姫リンゴ。アラティリスや小型の在来果物を指すことが多い小さなリンゴ状の果物。	Nagpupo ang mga bata og mansanitas sa ilang bakuran.
23430	23430	mandarin orange, tangerine. Small sweet citrus fruit with loose easily peeled orange skin.	マンダリンオレンジ（タンジェリン）。薄く剥きやすい橙色の皮を持つ小さくて甘い柑橘類。	Nagpalit siya og karanghita para sa iyang mga anak.
23431	23431	ponkan mandarin, Chinese orange. Variety of mandarin orange with sweet juice and easily removed rind.	ポンカン（中国産オレンジ）。甘い果汁と剥きやすい皮を持つマンダリンオレンジの一品種。	Lami ang ponkan nga gipalit niya sa Cebu Carbon.
23432	23432	tangelo citrus hybrid fruit. Hybrid citrus fruit cross between tangerine and pomelo with sweet flavor.	タンジェロ（柑橘系ハイブリッド）。タンジェリンとポメロを掛け合わせた甘みのあるハイブリッド柑橘類。	Bag-o pa lang niya nahibaw-an nga mayroon diay tangelo.
23433	23433	citrus fruit, general citrus. General term covering all sour or sweet citrus fruits like lime and orange.	柑橘類の総称。ライムやオレンジなどすべての酸味または甘みのある柑橘類をまとめて指す言葉。	Maayo ang citrus nga prutas alang sa immune system.
23434	23434	small banana variety. Small finger-sized banana variety with sweet flavor eaten as snack.	小型バナナの品種。おやつとして食べる甘い小型の指サイズのバナナの品種。	Paborito sa mga bata ang sagingsaging nga gikan sa uma.
23435	23435	calamansi variant, small lime. Variant spelling or regional name for the small Philippine citrus calamansi.	カラマンシーの変種（小型ライム）。小型フィリピン柑橘類カラマンシーの異表記または地域名。	Gipigang niya ang kalamansing sa ibabaw sa pagkaon.
23436	23436	pomelo, citron fruit. Large citrus fruit with thick spongy rind and mildly sweet juicy flesh.	ポメロ（シトロン）。厚くスポンジ状の皮と穏やかに甘くみずみずしい果肉を持つ大型柑橘類。	Gihatag niya ang suwa sa iyang pamilya isip merienda.
23437	23437	smooth-skinned fruit. Describes a fruit with smooth unblemished skin indicating good quality.	（果物の）表面が滑らか。傷のない滑らかな皮を持ち、品質の良さを示す果物を表す形容詞。	Pilia ang kinis nga mangga para mas lami pagkaon.
23438	23438	red, reddish colored fruit. Describes a fruit with red or reddish color indicating ripeness.	赤い、赤みがかった（果物）。熟れを示す赤または赤みがかった色の果物を表す形容詞。	Mapula na ang mga sineguelas busa puwede nang kaonon.
23439	23439	sour, acidic tasting. Describes the sharp sour taste of unripe or naturally acidic fruits.	酸っぱい、酸味がある。未熟または本来酸味のある果物の鋭い酸っぱい味を表す形容詞。	Aslom ang calamansi busa dili siya mokaon niini nga hilaw.
23440	23440	pithy, bland, hollow fruit. Describes a fruit that is dry or pithy inside without much sweet flavor.	スが入っている、水っぽい、味が薄い（果物）。内部が乾燥してスが入り、甘みや風味がほとんどない果物を表す形容詞。	Mahangin ang mansanas nga gipalit niya kay daan na kaayo.
23441	23441	overripe, too soft fruit. Describes a fruit that has become too soft or fermented beyond peak ripeness.	熟れすぎた、柔らかすぎる（果物）。最盛期を過ぎて柔らかくなりすぎたり発酵し始めたりした果物を表す形容詞。	Lutasa na ang saging busa dili na nako gusto kaunon.
23442	23442	something eaten, food consumed. Refers to food or fruit that has been or is being eaten.	食べられるもの、食べた食べ物。食べられた、または食べている最中の食べ物や果物を指す。	Prutas ang iyang kinaon sa matag buntag pagmata.
23443	23443	bunch of bananas, whole cluster. An entire bunch or cluster of bananas as harvested from the banana plant.	バナナの房（全体）。バナナの木から収穫したバナナ一本全体の房または塊。	Gipalit niya ang tinapok nga saging para sa tindahan.
23444	23444	hand of bananas, smaller cluster. One smaller cluster or hand of bananas broken off from the whole bunch.	バナナの一房（小さなまとまり）。全体の房から切り離した、バナナの小さなひとまとまり。	Gipalit lang niya ang usa ka sighing nga saging.
23445	23445	source tree, fruit source. The tree or plant from which fruit originates or is harvested.	元の木、果物の出どころ。果物が実ったり収穫されたりする木や植物。	Nahibaw-an niya ang tinubdan sa maayong manga sa ilang lugar.
23446	23446	edible, safe to eat. Describes a fruit that is safe and appropriate for eating or consumption.	食べられる、食べても安全。食用として安全で適切な果物を表す形容詞。	Kanolon na ang mga bayabas nga nagbunga sa bukid.
23447	23447	fruited, bore fruit. Describes a tree or plant that has produced or is producing fruit.	実がなった、果実を結んだ。木や植物が果実を実らせたことを表す。	Nangbunga na ang kahoy nga atis nga gibuhat nila.
23448	23448	bearing fruit, producing fruit. Describes the ongoing process of a plant or tree bearing fruit.	実をつけている、果実を産出中。植物や木が継続的に実をつけている過程を表す。	Nagpamunga na ang ilang bagong tanomang mangga.
23449	23449	orchard, fruit garden. A plot of land where fruit trees or plants are cultivated for harvest.	果樹園、果物畑。収穫のために果樹や果物の植物を栽培している土地。	Daghan og lain-laing prutas ang tanoman ni Lolo sa probinsya.
23450	23450	anise, star anise plant. Spice plant whose seeds resemble small fruits used in flavoring.	アニス（スターアニス）。風味付けに使われる小さな種を持つスパイス植物。	Gibutang niya ang anis sa kendi nga gihimo niya.
23451	23451	small fruit, tiny fruit piece. A very small fruit or tiny piece of fruit eaten as a snack.	小さな果物、果物の小片。おやつとして食べる非常に小さな果物や果物の小さなかけら。	Nagkuha siya og mumo nga aratilis gikan sa kahoy.
23452	23452	bland, tasteless, not sweet. Describes a fruit with little or no sweetness or flavor when expected.	味が薄い、甘みがない（果物）。期待されるほどの甘さや風味がほとんどない果物を表す形容詞。	Pasaw kaayo ang pakwan nga among gipalit, kulang og tam-is.
23453	23453	to ripen, allow to ripen. The act of allowing or waiting for fruit to reach full ripeness.	熟させる、熟すのを待つ。果物が十分に熟すまで待ったり熟成させたりする行為。	Gipabilin niya ang mangga para nanog una sa dili pa kaonon.
23454	23454	fruit pulp, fibrous fruit interior. The soft inner flesh or pulp of a fruit especially when fibrous.	果物の果肉、繊維質の内部。果物の柔らかい内側の果肉、特に繊維質のもの。	Lami ang buwa sa guyabano kung gipalma na ang liso.
23455	23455	dried fruit snack, candied fruit. Fruit that has been dried or candied as a preserved snack food.	ドライフルーツ菓子、砂糖漬けの果物。保存食として乾燥または砂糖漬けにした果物のおやつ。	Nagpalit siya og tikad nga mangga sa pasalubong shop.
23456	23456	fruit jam, fruit jelly. Sweet thick preserve made from cooked fruit and sugar spread on bread.	フルーツジャム・ゼリー。果物と砂糖を煮詰めてパンに塗る甘い濃厚な保存食。	Gihimo niya og halaya gikan sa bayabas para sa tinapay.
23457	23457	compote, stewed fruit dessert. Dessert made from whole or cut fruits cooked gently in sugar syrup.	コンポート（煮込み果物デザート）。果物をまるごとまたは切って砂糖シロップでやわらかく煮たデザート。	Niluto siya og kompota nga pinaghalong lain-laing prutas.
23458	23458	fruit salad, mixed fruit dish. A dish made from mixing various cut fresh fruits together, often with dressing.	フルーツサラダ、混合果物料理。様々な種類の新鮮な果物を切って混ぜ合わせた料理で、ドレッシングをかけることもある。	Gihimo niya og ensalada nga prutas para sa birthday party.
23459	23459	to share fruit, to distribute. The act of sharing harvested fruit among family members or neighbors.	果物を分け合う、配る。収穫した果物を家族や近隣の人々で分け合う行為。	Nagpakig-angay siya og mangga sa iyang mga silingan.
23460	23460	broken open fruit, cracked fruit. A fruit that has cracked or broken open, often due to overripeness.	割れた果物、裂けた果物。熟れすぎなどが原因で割れたり裂けたりした果物。	Bunhak na ang niyog busa gikuha na niya ang tubig niini.
23461	23461	left to ripen naturally. Fruit that was intentionally left to ripen naturally without interference.	自然に熟すままに放置された。自然に熟すよう意図的にそのままにされた果物。	Gipalamboy niya ang mangga sa kahoy hangtod hinog na kaayo.
23462	23462	future harvest, next fruiting. Referring to the next expected fruit harvest from trees or plants.	次回の収穫、次の実りの季節。木や植物から次に期待される果物の収穫を指す。	Mas daghan unta ang kinabukasan nga bunga sa among kahoy.
23463	23463	fruit grower, fruit farmer. A farmer who specializes in growing and cultivating fruit for sale.	果物農家、果物栽培者。販売目的で果物を専門に栽培している農家。	Ang magbubunga sa Davao nakapadaog sa kompetensya sa prutas.
23464	23464	fruit with bruises, bumped fruit. Describes fruit that has been bruised or damaged by impact.	傷のある果物、打撲のある果物。衝撃によって傷ついたり損傷を受けたりした果物を表す形容詞。	Dili ko mopalit og matumbok nga saging kay madali ra mangdaut.
23465	23465	spoiled, gone bad, rotted. Describes fruit that has rotted or spoiled and is no longer edible.	腐った、傷んだ、腐敗した。腐ったり傷んだりして食べられなくなった果物を表す。	Nabaho na ang papaya nga gibitin sa lababo.
23466	23466	fell from tree, dropped fruit. Describes fruit that has fallen off naturally from the tree.	木から落ちた、落下した果物。木から自然に落ちた果物を表す。	Nabuong ang daghan nga mangga tungod sa kusog nga hangin.
23467	23467	was eaten, has been consumed. Past completed form indicating the fruit has already been eaten.	食べられた、食べ終えられた。果物がすでに食べられたことを示す完了過去形。	Kinani na tanan ang lansones nga gipalit ni Nanay kagahapon.
25171	25171	rice mill or grinder. A device used for husking or grinding rice into flour.	精米機または製粉機。米の籾殻を取り除いたり、小麦粉に挽いたりするための装置。	Gidala nila ang humay sa kiskisan.
25172	25172	splatter or spray from cooking. The oil or liquid that splashes out from a hot pan while cooking.	調理中の油はねや液体の飛び散り。加熱中のフライパンから飛び散る油や液体。	Nasakitan siya sa tigsik sa lana sa kawali.
25173	25173	kerosene stove. A small stove that burns kerosene used for cooking in homes.	灯油コンロ。家庭での調理に使う、灯油を燃料とする小型コンロ。	Gigamit pa nila ang siyansi tungod kay naigo ang kuryente.
25174	25174	teakettle or kettle. A pot with a spout used for boiling water for tea or coffee.	やかん。お茶やコーヒー用の湯を沸かすための注ぎ口付きポット。	Gibutang niya ang talyasi sa estobo para sa mainit nga tsa.
25175	25175	thermos or insulated bottle. An insulated container used for keeping liquids hot or cold.	魔法瓶または保温ボトル。飲み物を温かく、または冷たく保つための断熱容器。	Gibutangan niya og kape ang termo para sa biyahe.
25176	25176	glass jar or bottle. A glass container used for storing or preserving food items.	ガラス瓶またはガラス容器。食品の保存や貯蔵に使うガラス製の容器。	Gibutangan niya og asukal ang garapa.
25177	25177	funnel. A cone-shaped kitchen tool used for pouring liquids into containers.	じょうご（ファネル）。液体を容器に注ぎ入れるための円錐形の調理道具。	Gigamit niya ang imbudo sa pagbutang og lana sa bote.
25178	25178	wide shallow pan. A flat or shallow pan used for frying or sautéing food.	浅型の広口鍋。炒め物や揚げ物に使う、平らで浅いフライパン。	Gisalod niya ang gulay sa luwag nga kawali.
25179	25179	tray for serving food. A flat rectangular tray used for carrying or serving food and drinks.	食事用トレー。料理や飲み物を運んだり提供したりするための平らな長方形のトレー。	Gibutang niya ang mga tasa sa eplayan.
25180	25180	serving platter or tray. A large flat dish or tray used for serving food at the table.	サービングプラターまたはトレー。食卓で料理を盛り付けて提供するための大きな平皿またはトレー。	Gibutang niya ang lechon sa bandehado.
25181	25181	teaspoon. A small spoon used for measuring or stirring tea, coffee, or medicine.	ティースプーン。お茶・コーヒー・薬などを量ったりかき混ぜたりする小さなスプーン。	Gidugang niya og usa ka kutsarita nga asin sa sopas.
25182	25182	tablespoon or large spoon. A larger spoon used for serving or measuring larger amounts of food.	大さじまたは大型スプーン。料理の盛り付けや多めの分量を量るための大きなスプーン。	Tagduha ka kutsaron sa asukar ang akong recipe.
25183	25183	brush for washing dishes. A brush used to scrub and clean pots, pans, and dishes.	食器洗いブラシ。鍋・フライパン・食器をこすって洗うためのブラシ。	Gigamit niya ang sipilyo sa paghugas sa kaldero.
25184	25184	scrubbing pad or sponge. A rough sponge or pad used for scrubbing dirty dishes.	スコアリングパッドまたはスポンジ。汚れた食器をこすり洗いするための粗いスポンジやパッド。	Gigamit niya ang estropada aron mapula ang mantsa sa plato.
25185	25185	dishwashing soap. Soap used specifically for washing dishes, pots, and utensils.	食器用洗剤。食器・鍋・調理器具を洗うための専用石鹸。	Gidugang niya ang sapbon sa tubig aron mahugas ang pinggan.
23471	23471	easy to split open fruit. Describes a fruit whose skin or husk is easy to crack open.	割りやすい果物。皮や殻が手で簡単に割れる果物を表す。	Tublihon kaayo ang lansones busa magaan lang itibhat.
23472	23472	fruit heap, pile of fruits. A pile or heap of fruits gathered together for sale or storage.	果物の山、果物の積み上げ。販売や保管のために集められた果物の山。	Dako ang buntod nga mangga nga gibaligya sa merkado.
23473	23473	to split open fruit by hand. To crack or split open the husk or skin of fruit using hands or tools.	手で果物を割り開く。手や道具を使って果物の殻や皮を割る。	Gitibhang niya ang lansones gamit lang ang iyang mga tudlo.
23474	23474	to share fruits, to divide equally. Sharing or dividing fruits equally among several people.	果物を分け合う、均等に分ける。果物を複数の人の間で均等に分配する。	Nagpakigbahin siya og mangga sa tanan nila nga magsuon.
23475	23475	fruit stall, place to buy fruits. A dedicated area or stall in the market where fruits are sold.	果物売り場、果物販売所。市場内で果物を販売する専用の場所や屋台。	Nag-adto sila sa tikasan aron mopalit og lain-laing prutas.
23476	23476	cause to ripen, force-ripen. The act of inducing or accelerating ripening in fruits through chemicals or methods.	果物を熟させる、人工的に追熟させる。薬品や方法を用いて果物の熟成を促進・加速させる。	Gipahitas-on nila ang mangga gamit ang carbide aron mabaligya dayon.
23477	23477	unhusked rice, palay. Raw rice still in its husk, harvested from the field.	もみ殻付きの米、籾米。収穫したままの籾殻のついた生の米。	Nag-ani sila og humay sa uma kagahapon.
23478	23478	milled white rice. Rice that has been husked and milled, ready for cooking.	精白米。籾殻を取り除き精米した、調理可能な白米。	Palita kog usa ka kilo nga bugas sa tindahan.
23479	23479	cooked rice. Rice that has been boiled or steamed and is ready to eat.	炊いたご飯。茹でまたは蒸して食べられる状態になった米。	Luto na ang kan-on, kaon na ta.
23480	23480	cassava. A starchy root crop widely used in making food and snacks.	キャッサバ。食品や軽食の製造に広く使われるでんぷん質の根菜。	Nagtanom si Tatay og balanghoy sa garden.
23481	23481	taro cooked in coconut milk. A traditional Cebuano dish made from taro leaves cooked in coconut milk.	ティヌモック。タロイモの葉をココナッツミルクで煮たセブアノの伝統料理。	Ang tinumok usa ka lutoon nga may dahon sa gabi.
23482	23482	sweet potato tops as food. Young leaves and shoots of the kamote plant, eaten as vegetable.	サツマイモの葉の食材。カモテの若葉や新芽を野菜として食べたもの。	Giluto niya ang nidog-nidog sa kamote alang sa paniudto.
23483	23483	rice plant, paddy. The rice plant growing in the field before harvest.	稲、水田稲。収穫前に田んぼで育っている稲の植物。	Maayo ang pagay karong tuiga tungod sa daghang ulan.
23484	23484	harvest. The act or season of collecting ripened crops from the field.	収穫。田畑から熟した作物を取り入れる行為または季節。	Daghang bugas ang ani nila karong tuiga.
23485	23485	harvester, reaper. A person who harvests rice or other crops in the field.	収穫者、刈り取り人。田んぼで稲やその他の作物を収穫する人。	Ang mga mag-aani nanganhi gikan sa silingang barangay.
23486	23486	milled rice bran. The outer layer removed during rice milling, often fed to animals.	米糠。精米時に取り除かれる外皮で、主に家畜の飼料となる。	Gigamit ang lutos sa pagpakaon sa mga baboy.
23487	23487	rice water, rice washing. Water used to wash rice before cooking, sometimes used for skin care.	米のとぎ汁。炊飯前に米を洗った水で、肌のケアにも使われることがある。	Gigamit niya ang inum-inum sa paghugas sa iyang nawong.
23488	23488	young rice stalks. The early seedlings of rice before transplanting to the main field.	稲の若苗。本田への移植前の稲の初期苗。	Gibalhin na nila ang banig-banig sa rice paddy.
23489	23489	rice seedbed. A small plot where rice seeds are germinated before transplanting.	稲の苗床。稲を発芽させてから移植するための小さな育苗区画。	Andam na ang sumalagi para sa pagpugas.
23490	23490	rice mill. A machine or facility used to mill or process harvested rice.	精米所。収穫した米を精米・加工する機械や施設。	Gidala nila ang humay sa gilingan aron mahimong bugas.
23491	23491	planting season. The time of year designated for sowing or planting crops.	植え付け時期。作物の種まきや植え付けに定められた時期。	Abli na ang kagamhanan, kinahanglan nang magtanom.
23492	23492	to harvest crops. To gather or collect mature crops from the agricultural field.	作物を収穫する。農地から成熟した作物を刈り取り集める。	Mag-abot na sila sa humay karong semana.
23493	23493	wooden mortar for rice. A large wooden bowl used together with a pestle to pound unhusked rice.	木製の臼。籾米をつく際に杵と共に使う大きな木製の容器。	Gibutang niya ang humay sa lusong aron labugon.
23494	23494	rice straw. The dried stalks of rice plants left after harvesting the grain.	稲わら。収穫後に残る稲植物の乾燥した茎。	Gisunog nila ang igot pagkatapos sa ani.
23495	23495	corn grits, coarse cornmeal. Coarsely ground dried corn used as a staple food in Cebuano households.	コーングリッツ、粗びきトウモロコシ粉。セブアノの家庭で主食として使われる粗びき乾燥トウモロコシ。	Linuto si Nanay og ugbo para sa paniudto.
23496	23496	corn cob. The hard central core of a corn ear after the kernels are removed.	トウモロコシの芯。実を取り除いたトウモロコシの硬い中心部。	Gigamit ang bagol-bagol sa pagsugnod og kalayo.
23497	23497	ear of corn. The fruit of the corn plant containing the kernels arranged on a cob.	トウモロコシの穂。実が芯に並んで付いたトウモロコシの果実。	Nag-ihaw sila og butong sa ihawanan.
23498	23498	steamed rice cake. A traditional Filipino steamed cake made from ground rice flour.	プト。米粉を蒸して作るフィリピンの伝統的な蒸し菓子。	Gipalit niya ang puto sa merkado para sa pamahaw.
23499	23499	sticky rice cake in coconut. A sweet delicacy made from glutinous rice, coconut milk, and sugar.	ビコ。もち米、ココナッツミルク、砂糖で作る甘い伝統菓子。	Naghimo si Lola og biko para sa piyesta.
23500	23500	flat rice cake in coconut. A flat boiled rice cake rolled in grated coconut and sugar.	パリタウ。茹でた平たい米菓子をすりおろしたココナッツと砂糖で和えたもの。	Maayo ang palitaw nga may latik sa ibabaw.
23501	23501	sticky rice roll in banana leaf. Glutinous rice wrapped in banana leaves and steamed until cooked.	スマン。バナナの葉に包んで蒸したもち米の伝統菓子。	Gipalit nila ang suman sa peryahan sa fiesta.
23502	23502	rice cake baked on charcoal. A traditional rice cake baked between charcoal layers, often with toppings.	ビビンカ。炭火で焼いたフィリピンの伝統的な米ケーキ。	Lami kaayo ang bibingka nga mainit pa.
23503	23503	rice porridge, lugaw. A thick rice congee usually eaten when sick or as a comfort food.	米のお粥、濃いおかゆ。病気の時や日常の慰め食として食べる濃いご飯のおかゆ。	Giluto niya og pospas ang bata nga may sakit.
23504	23504	rice porridge with ginger. Watery cooked rice seasoned with ginger, often given to the ill.	生姜入りのご飯粥。生姜で味付けした薄いご飯粥で、病人に与えることが多い。	Niluto si Inay og lugaw para sa masakiton nga amahan.
23505	23505	glutinous rice, sticky rice. A variety of rice with high starch content that becomes sticky when cooked.	もち米、糯米。炊くと粘りが出る高でんぷん質の米の品種。	Gigamit ang tapol sa paghimo og biko ug suman.
23506	23506	sticky rice variety. Another term for glutinous rice used in various sweet rice delicacies.	もち米の品種。各種甘いもち米菓子に使うもう一つのもち米の呼び名。	Adunay malagkit nga bugas sa tindahan.
23507	23507	boiled or steamed food. Food cooked by boiling or steaming, often referring to rice or vegetables.	茹でたまたは蒸した料理。米や野菜などを茹でるまたは蒸して調理した食べ物。	Nagluto siya og sinaing nga kamote para sa hapunan.
23508	23508	boiled until soft. Describing food cooked by boiling until it becomes tender and soft.	柔らかく茹でた。茹でて柔らかくなるまで調理された食べ物を表す。	Nilubog na ang balanghoy, puwede na kaonon.
23509	23509	cassava flour or starch. Starch extracted from cassava root, used for cooking and baking.	キャッサバの粉またはでんぷん。調理や製菓に使うキャッサバの根から取ったでんぷん。	Gigamit ang harina sa balanghoy sa paghimo og puto.
23510	23510	starch from root crops. Pure white starch derived from cassava or other root crops.	根菜でんぷん。キャッサバなどの根菜から抽出した純白のでんぷん。	Gigamit ang almirol sa pag-ihon sa sinina.
23511	23511	pounded, hulled. Describing rice that has been manually pounded to remove its husk.	搗いた、脱穀した。手作業でついて籾殻を取り除いた米を表す。	Lami ang kan-on nga gikan sa nilabog nga humay.
23512	23512	to peel root crops. To remove the outer skin of root vegetables before cooking.	根菜の皮をむく。調理前に根菜の外皮を取り除く。	Gitalop niya ang balanghoy ug kamote bago iluto.
23513	23513	shared land for farming. Agricultural land shared between landowner and tenant farmer for crops.	小作地、農業用共有地。地主と小作農が作物を分け合う農業用共有の土地。	Nag-uma siya sa buhisan sa iyang amahan.
