24339	24339	pounded toasted young rice. Young glutinous rice that is toasted and pounded flat into flakes.	ピニピグ。若いもち米を焙煎して平たく搗き潰したフレーク状のもの。	Gibutangan og pinipig ang tsokolate alang sa dugang nga lami.
24340	24340	toasted rice, roasted rice. Rice that has been dry-toasted in a pan until lightly browned and fragrant.	炒り米、煎り米。フライパンで乾煎りして薄く色づき香ばしくなった米。	Ang sinanlag nga bugas ginagamit sa pag-imbento og kape-kape.
24341	24341	rice cooked in bamboo tube. Glutinous rice stuffed and cooked inside a bamboo tube over fire.	竹筒飯。もち米を竹筒に詰めて火で炊いたもの。	Naghimo sila og inubaran didto sa kampo sa kabukiran.
24342	24342	rice cooked in corn oil. Traditional method of cooking rice with coconut or corn oil for richer flavor.	油で炊いたご飯。ご飯をコーンオイルやヤシ油で炊く伝統的な調理法で、風味豊かに仕上がる。	Mas manamit ang loto kaysa ordinaryong niluto nga kan-on.
24343	24343	to eat rice or a meal. To eat, specifically used when consuming rice or a full meal.	ご飯を食べる、食事をする。特にご飯や食事全般を食べる際に使う。	Kanen na ta kay gutumon na ko.
24344	24344	meal, act of eating. The act of eating a meal, particularly a rice-centered meal.	食事、食事の行為。特にご飯を中心とした食事をとること。	Ang pangaon sa buntag importante kaayo sa lawas.
24345	24345	lunch, midday meal. The noon meal, usually the heaviest rice-based meal of the day.	昼食、昼ご飯。正午の食事で、通常一日の中で最も充実したご飯中心の食事。	Nakaon na ba kamo sa inyong paniudto?
24346	24346	afternoon snack, light snack. Light snack eaten between meals, often rice cakes or other light foods.	おやつ、軽食。食事と食事の間に食べる軽い間食で、米菓子などが多い。	Ang puto ug bibingka ginagamit sa merienda sa hapon.
24347	24347	rice gruel water, starchy water. The starchy water drained from washing or cooking rice.	とぎ汁、でんぷん水。米を洗ったり炊いたりする際に出るでんぷん質の水。	Ang pampaet ginagamit usahay sa paglinis og damit.
