24349	24349	large cooking pot. Large pot used for cooking rice or preparing large quantities of food.	大鍋。ご飯を炊いたり大量の料理を作ったりするための大きな鍋。	Gitambok niya ang kaldero og bugas para sa daghan nga bisita.
24350	24350	rice scoop, ladle for rice. Scoop or ladle used to serve cooked rice from the pot into plates.	しゃもじ、ご飯用のおたま。鍋から炊いたご飯を皿によそうためのすくい道具。	Gamiti ang kuhon sa pag-kuhit og kan-on sa plato.
24351	24351	mat, drying mat for rice. Woven mat sometimes used for drying harvested rice grains under the sun.	ゴザ、米の乾燥用むしろ。収穫した籾を日干しにする際に使う編んだむしろ。	Gibay-an nila ang humay sa banig para mauga.
24352	24352	mortar and pestle for rice. Stone mortar and pestle traditionally used for pounding rice.	米用の臼と杵。米を搗くために伝統的に使われる石製の臼と杵。	Gibagtik niya ang pilit gamit ang almiris para sa palitaw.
24353	24353	rice-pounding activity, pounding rice. The traditional activity of pounding rice using mortar and pestle.	米搗き、米を搗く作業。臼と杵を使って米を搗く伝統的な作業。	Naghimo sila og bayuhan sa humay para mahimong bugas.
24354	24354	rice grains, raw rice. Alternative term for raw rice grains, used in some Cebuano dialects.	米粒、生米。一部のセブアノ方言で使われる、炊く前の生の米粒を指す言葉。	Gipalit niya og bigas sa tindahan para sa panulundon.
24355	24355	steamed bun with filling. Steamed Chinese-style bun with meat filling, eaten as breakfast or snack.	肉まん、蒸しパン。具入りの中華風蒸しパンで、朝食や軽食として食べる。	Nangaon siya og siopao uban sa kape sa pamahaw.
24356	24356	ox tripe rice porridge. Rice porridge cooked with ox tripe, popular breakfast dish in markets.	ゴトー。牛モツ入りのライスポリッジで、市場で人気の朝食料理。	Nakaon sila og goto sa karinderya sa buntag.
24357	24357	sticky rice cooked in coconut milk. Festive glutinous rice dish cooked with coconut milk wrapped in banana leaf.	ブリンヘ。ココナッツミルクで炊いてバナナの葉で包んだ祝い用のもち米料理。	Gihimo ni Lola ang bringhe para sa Pasko nga pagtitipon.
24358	24358	toasted rice flour candy roll. Cylindrical rice cake made from toasted glutinous rice flour and coconut milk.	エスパソル。焙煎したもち米粉とヤシミルクで作る円筒形の米菓子。	Gisapot nila ang espasol sa toasted rice flour bag-o ibaligya.
24359	24359	sticky sweet rice delicacy. Sweet thick paste made from glutinous rice, coconut milk, and sugar.	カラマイ。もち米、ヤシミルク、砂糖で作る甘くて濃厚なペースト状の菓子。	Bantayan nga baligya og kalamay ang Bohol sa tibuok Pilipinas.
24360	24360	layered rice cake dessert. Colorful layered glutinous rice cake with different flavors and colors.	サピン・サピン。異なる味と色が重なった彩り豊かなもち米の層菓子。	Ang sapin-sapin nga may kulay maoy nahimo nila para sa handaan.
24361	24361	brown rice cake with lye. Sticky brown steamed rice cake made with lye water, topped with grated coconut.	クッチンタ。灰汁水で作る茶色い蒸し米菓子で、すりおろしたヤシをのせて食べる。	Giluom niya ang kutsinta sa bago nga niyog human maluto.
24362	24362	steamed rice cake with molasses. Variant spelling of kutsinta, a steamed glutinous rice cake with brown sugar.	クッチンタ（別綴り）。黒糖を使った蒸しもち米菓子で、クッチンタの異なる綴り。	Gipalit niya og cuchinta sa tiendahan para sa merienda.
24363	24363	pounded young corn or rice delicacy. Traditional Visayan delicacy made from pounded young corn or sticky rice.	バエ・バエ。若いトウモロコシやもち米を搗いて作るビサヤ伝統の菓子。	Bantayon kaayong baligya ang baye-baye sa mga produkto sa Leyte.
24364	24364	sticky rice ball sweet. Small glutinous rice ball filled with sweet paste, a rice-based snack.	パニャム。甘いあんを詰めた小さなもち米団子。米を使った菓子。	Gipalit siya og panyam sa Chinese store para sa merienda.
24365	24365	already eaten, rice already consumed. Describes food or rice that has already been eaten or consumed.	食べ終わった、すでに食べたご飯。すでに食べられて消費された食べ物やご飯を指す。	Namaos na ang kan-on busa walay makaon ang ulahing miabot.
24366	24366	appetite, desire to eat. Appetite or eagerness to eat rice and other food.	食欲、食べたいという欲求。ご飯や食べ物を食べたいという意欲や食欲。	Way gana siya og kaon tungod kay may sakit siya.
