24387	24387	sweet, sweet-tasting rice cake. Describes a sweet rice preparation or rice cake that has pleasant sweetness.	甘い、甘味のある。米菓子やご飯の調理品がほどよい甘さを持つ様子。	Matam-is kaayo ang biko nga gihimo ni Lola para sa Pasko.
24388	24388	to sauté, fry with garlic. To sauté ingredients in oil with garlic and onion before mixing with rice.	炒める、ガーリック炒めにする。ニンニクと玉ねぎを油で炒め、ご飯と混ぜる前に具材を炒める。	Gisaa ang sibuyas ug bawang bag-o isangag ang kan-on.
24389	24389	raw marinated seafood with rice. Raw fish or seafood marinated in vinegar, often eaten as viand with rice.	キラウ、酢漬け生魚介。魚や魚介を酢でマリネした料理で、ご飯のおかずとして食べる。	Ang kilaw nga isda masarap kaayong kaonon uban sa kan-on.
24390	24390	sauce poured over rice. Any sauce or gravy poured over rice to enhance flavor.	ソース、ご飯にかけるたれ。ご飯の風味を引き立てるためにかけるソースやグレービー。	Gibubo niya ang sarsa sa ibabaw sa kan-on para mas manamit.
24391	24391	purple rice variety. Purple-colored rice variety used in making specialty rice dishes and cakes.	紫米の品種。特別な米料理や米菓子に使われる紫色の米の品種。	Gigamit ang duhat-bugas sa paghimo og puto bumbong.
24392	24392	to store, to preserve rice. To store or preserve rice properly to maintain its freshness and quality.	米を保存する、貯蔵する。米の鮮度と品質を保つために適切に保存する。	Imbaka ang sobrang kan-on sa ref para dili mabulok.
24393	24393	lacking rice, without enough food. Describes a state of having insufficient rice or food for a meal.	米が不足している、食料が足りない。食事に必要な米や食料が不十分な状態。	Kabos sila og pagkaon busa dili sila makakaon og kan-on adlaw-adlaw.
24394	24394	leftover cold rice. Cold leftover rice from the previous meal, often reheated or made into sinangag.	残りご飯、冷やご飯。前の食事で残った冷たいご飯で、温め直したりチャーハンにしたりする。	Ang bahaw nga kan-on i-sangag na lang para sa pamahaw.
24395	24395	fond of eating rice, always hungry. Describes a person who loves to eat rice and is frequently hungry.	ご飯好きの、いつもお腹が空いている。ご飯を食べることが好きで、よく空腹になる人を表す。	Palaon kaayo ang akong anak busa daghan gyod og kan-on ang kinahanglan.
24396	24396	to fill pot with rice and water. To fill a cooking pot with rice and the appropriate amount of water.	鍋に米と水を入れる。炊飯用の鍋に米と適量の水を入れる。	Tambonga ang palayok og bugas ug tubig para maluto.
24397	24397	flavored rice, seasoned rice. Describes rice that has been seasoned or mixed with flavoring ingredients.	味付きご飯、味付けされた。調味料や香味食材で味付けされたご飯を表す。	Tinimplahan ang kan-on gamit ang pampalasa para mas manamit.
24398	24398	collection of viands for rice. Various dishes prepared to be eaten alongside rice in a meal.	おかず類、副菜一式。食事でご飯と一緒に食べるために用意された様々な料理。	Daghan ang sud-anan nga giandam alang sa fiesta kauban ang kan-on.
24399	24399	favorite rice dish or food. Describes a preferred or favorite rice preparation or rice-based dish.	お気に入りの、好きな。好みのご飯料理や米を使った料理を表す。	Ang sinangag maoy paborito niyang pamahaw sa buntag.
24400	24400	eating habit, rice eating custom. Custom or habit of eating rice, a cultural practice in Cebuano life.	食習慣、米食の慣習。セブアノの生活における米を食べる習慣や文化的な慣わし。	Ang gawi sa Cebuano magkaon og kan-on sa tanan nga pagkaon.
24401	24401	stove, cooking stove for rice. Cooking stove or fire source used for boiling or steaming rice.	かまど、炊飯用コンロ。米を炊いたり蒸したりするための調理用コンロや火元。	Gibutang niya ang palayok sa kalan para maluto ang kan-on.
24402	24402	clay cooking pot for rice. Traditional earthen clay pot used for cooking rice and other foods.	土鍋、米炊き用の素焼き鍋。米やその他の料理を炊くのに使う伝統的な素焼きの土鍋。	Mas matam-is ang kan-on kung niluto sa palayok kaysa metal nga kaldero.
24403	24403	crushed rice, broken rice grains. Broken or crushed rice grains that result from milling or pounding.	砕け米、割れた米粒。精米や搗き加工の際に生じた割れた米粒。	Ang durog nga bugas ginagamit sa lugaw kaysa butil nga bugas.
24404	24404	oily, buttery rice preparation. Describes rice preparations that are rich with oil or butter.	油っこい、バター風味の。油やバターをたっぷり使ったご飯料理を表す。	Mantikada ang sinangag tungod sa daghang lana nga gigamit.
24405	24405	to feed someone rice. To feed rice or a meal to another person, especially a child or sick person.	ご飯を食べさせる。子どもや病人など他の人にご飯や食事を食べさせる。	Gipinakaon niya og kan-on ang iyang inahan nga tigulang na.
24406	24406	rice harvest season, harvesting. The rice harvesting season when rice is reaped from the fields.	稲刈りの季節、収穫期。田んぼで稲を刈り取る米の収穫シーズン。	Ang umaanon maoy pinaka-busy nga panahon sa mag-uuma.
24407	24407	harvested rice, rice harvest. The harvested rice from the field after the growing season.	収穫米、取り入れた稲。栽培シーズン後に田んぼから収穫した米。	Daghan ang aning nila karong tuiga tungod sa maayong panahon.
24408	24408	rice husk, chaff. The outer husk or shell removed from rice during milling.	籾殻、糠。精米の際に米から取り除かれる外側の殻。	Ang tahop ginagamit puhon sa pamulbo sa mga halaman.
24409	24409	carefully cooked, well-prepared rice. Describes rice that has been carefully and properly cooked with attention.	丁寧に炊かれた、よく調理された。手をかけて丁寧に炊き上げたご飯を表す。	Inampingon ang kan-on nga gihimo ni Nanay para sa bisita.
24410	24410	livelihood based on rice. Way of life or livelihood centered on rice farming or rice trade.	米を基盤とした生計、暮らし。稲作や米の売買を中心とした生活様式や生計手段。	Ang bugas maoy kinabuhian sa ilang pamilya sukad pa kaniadto.
24411	24411	boiled root crops eaten with rice. Boiled root crops served as supplement or alternative to rice during meals.	茹でた根菜類。食事でご飯の補足または代替として提供する茹でた根菜類。	Ang tinanok nga kamote gikauban sa kan-on sa kabos nga pamilya.
24412	24412	boiled dish eaten with rice. Simple boiled dish using vegetables or meat, eaten as viand with rice.	煮物料理。野菜や肉をシンプルに煮たもので、ご飯のおかずとして食べる。	Ang linat-an nga isda kauban ang kan-on maoy paborito ko.
24413	24413	slightly undercooked rice. Describes rice that is slightly undercooked and still has hard center.	やや生煮えのご飯。中心部が硬く、やや生煮えの状態のご飯を表す。	Gihaw pa ang kan-on busa isaulod pa og dyutay sa kalan.
