30599	30599	so, it turns out, realization. Discovery or realization particle indicating new information.	そうか、なるほど、〜だったのか。新しい情報や気づきを示す発見・了解の助詞。	Ikaw diay ang nagbuhat ana.
30600	30600	instead, rather, on the contrary. Contrastive particle indicating contrast or preference.	むしろ、かえって、それより。対比や選好を示す逆接助詞。	Dili ko moinom, mokaon hinuon ko.
30601	30601	actually, apparently, so it seems. Particle indicating a newly discovered or surprising fact.	実は、どうやら、〜らしい。新たに発見した事実や意外な情報を示す助詞。	Siya gali ang nagkuha.
30602	30602	because, since, for. Causal particle introducing reason or explanation.	〜だから、〜なので、〜ゆえに。理由や説明を導く原因助詞。	Moadto ko kay gusto ko.
30603	30603	reportedly, allegedly, they say. Reportive particle indicating hearsay or reported speech.	〜だそうだ、〜とのこと、〜らしい。伝聞や報告された情報を示す助詞。	Moabot kuno siya ugma.
30604	30604	reportedly, allegedly, they say. Hearsay or quotative particle indicating reported information.	〜だそうだ、〜とのこと、〜らしい。伝聞や引用された情報を示す助詞。	Maayo daw siya nga estudyante.
30605	30605	why, why is it that. Interrogative focus particle asking for reason or cause.	なぜ、どうして。理由や原因を尋ねる疑問焦点助詞。	Nganong wala ka mokaon?
30606	30606	that (focus), referring to something known. Demonstrative focus particle referring to something previously mentioned.	あの（焦点指示）。以前に言及されたものを指す指示焦点助詞。	Kanang libro ang akong giingon.
30607	30607	that is it, correct, that. Affirmative or equational particle meaning that is it or correct.	そうだ、正しい、それだ。「それが〜だ」「正しい」を意味する肯定・同一助詞。	Mao kana ang akong gusto.
30608	30608	only, just, merely. Formal limiting particle equivalent to lang or ra.	〜だけ、〜しか、ただ。langやraに相当する格式ある限定助詞。	Usa lamang ang akong gipangayo.
30609	30609	hopefully, I wish, please. Optative particle expressing hope, wish, or polite request.	〜だといいな、〜であってほしい、どうか。希望や願望、丁寧な依頼を表す希求助詞。	Moabot unta siya ugma.
30610	30610	hopefully, I wish, if only. Optative particle expressing a wish or unfulfilled desire.	〜だといいな、〜であればよかった。願望や叶わなかった望みを表す希求助詞。	Sana moabot siya sa oras.
30611	30611	why, for what reason. Interrogative focus particle asking for cause or reason.	なぜ、どういう理由で。理由や原因を尋ねる疑問焦点助詞。	Ngano wala ka motubag?
30612	30612	seems like, as if, apparently. Approximative particle indicating resemblance or impression.	〜みたいだ、〜のようだ、どうやら。類似や印象を示す概括助詞。	Murag dili siya moabot.
30613	30613	let us, suggestion marker, inclusive we. Inclusive suggestion or hortative particle meaning let's.	〜しよう（勧誘）。話し手と聞き手を含む「〜しよう」を意味する包括的勧誘助詞。	Moadto ta ugma.
30614	30614	future action marker, will. Verbal focus particle indicating future or non-past action.	〜するだろう（未来動作）。未来や非過去の動作を示す動詞焦点助詞。	Mo siya anha ugma.
30615	30615	ongoing action marker, doing. Aspect marker indicating present or ongoing action.	〜している（進行中の動作）。現在進行中の動作を示すアスペクト助詞。	Ga-kaon pa siya karon.
30616	30616	past action focus marker. Patient-focus past tense verbal prefix indicating completed action.	（過去の動作焦点標識）。完了した動作を示す患者焦点・過去時制の動詞接頭辞。	Gi-kaon niya ang tinapay.
30617	30617	ours, let us, that of ours. Inclusive possessive or suggestion particle.	私たちの〜、〜しよう（包括）。包括的な所有や提案を示す助詞。	Ato nang buhaton karon.
30618	30618	enough, sufficient, that is all. Limiting particle indicating sufficiency or completion.	十分、それで十分、以上。十分さや完了を示す限定助詞。	Taman na kana, ayaw pagdugang.
30619	30619	always, often, frequently. Frequency adverbial particle indicating habitual occurrence.	いつも、しょっちゅう、頻繁に。習慣的な出来事を示す頻度副詞助詞。	Pirme siya naa sa balay.
30620	30620	or, option marker. Disjunctive particle presenting alternatives or options.	または、〜か。選択肢や代替を示す選言助詞。	Mokaon ka o dili?
30621	30621	in fact, even, precisely. Emphatic particle intensifying or focusing a statement.	実に、〜でさえ、まさに。文を強調・焦点化する強調助詞。	Siya gani ang nagkuha sa akong bag.
30622	30622	purely, all of it, nothing but. Intensifying particle indicating exclusivity or completeness.	純粋に、全部、〜ばかり。排他性や完全性を示す強調助詞。	Puroha pagkaon ang iyang gibuhat.
30623	30623	I thought, I assumed, supposedly. Assumptive particle indicating a mistaken belief or assumption.	〜だと思っていた、てっきり〜だと。誤った思い込みや推測を示す仮定助詞。	Abi nako moadto siya.
30624	30624	reportedly, supposedly, they say. Variant of kuno; hearsay particle for reported information.	〜だそうだ、〜とのこと。kunoの異形；伝聞情報を示す助詞。	Maayo kunu ang iyang trabaho.
30625	30625	including, even, also. Inclusive particle adding another item to a set.	〜も含めて、〜でさえ、〜も。集合に別の要素を加える包括助詞。	Pati siya naapil sa problema.
30626	30626	including, together with. Inclusive particle indicating inclusion in a group.	〜を含めて、〜と一緒に。あるグループへの包含を示す助詞。	Lakip siya sa mga moadto.
30627	30627	doubtful, uncertain, hesitant. Particle or adjective expressing doubt or uncertainty.	疑わしい、不確かな、迷っている。疑念や不確実さを表す助詞または形容詞。	Duhaduha pa ko kung moadto.
30628	30628	maybe, perhaps, lest. Possibility or caution particle indicating uncertainty or warning.	もしかしたら、たぶん、〜しないように。不確かさや注意を示す可能性・警告の助詞。	Basin wala na siya didto.
30629	30629	you know, you see, right. Discourse particle seeking agreement or acknowledging shared knowledge.	〜でしょう、ご存知のとおり、ね。共通認識を確認したり同意を求めたりする談話助詞。	Kabalo ka man, dili ko ganahan.
30630	30630	no, not, nothing. Shortened informal variant of wala expressing negation.	ない、いない、なし。walaの短縮形で否定を表す助詞。	Wa ko kabalo ana.
30631	30631	not, no, negation. Shortened informal variant of dili expressing negation.	〜ない、いや（否定）。diliの短縮形で否定を表す助詞。	Di ko gusto ana.
30632	30632	not, no, negation. Variant negation particle used in some Visayan dialects.	〜ない、いや（否定）。一部のビサヤ方言で使われる否定助詞。	Indi ko moadto.
30633	30633	I don't know, beats me. Epistemic negation particle expressing ignorance or uncertainty.	知らない、わからない。無知や不確かさを表す認識的否定助詞。	Ambot kung moabot siya o dili.
30634	30634	focus affix for doer. Verbal focus prefix indicating the habitual agent of an action.	（動作主焦点接辞）。動作の習慣的な行為者を示す動詞焦点接頭辞。	Siya ang tig-lutok sa balay.
30635	30635	there it is, see, look. Demonstrative affirmative particle pointing out something evident.	ほらそこにある、見て、ほら。明白な事柄を指し示す指示肯定助詞。	Noa, mao diay ang akong gisulti.
30636	30636	hey, expressing mild realization. Discourse particle expressing mild surprise or realization.	あ、へえ（軽い気づき）。軽い驚きや気づきを表す談話助詞。	Hay, wala diay ko nahibalo.
30637	30637	well, go on, there you go. Particle expressing encouragement, warning, or consequence.	さあ、どうぞ、ほら（結果として）。激励・警告・結果を表す助詞。	Hala, sulayan na nato.
30638	30638	well, okay, alright then. Transitional affirmative particle indicating acceptance or transition.	では、わかった、それでは。受諾や話題転換を示す移行的肯定助詞。	Buweno, buhaton na nako kana.
30639	30639	not even, neither, nor. Negative particle indicating neither or not even one.	〜でさえない、〜も〜ない。「〜でさえない」「どちらも〜ない」を意味する否定助詞。	Ni usa wala siya moingon.
30640	30640	even though, although. Concessive particle acknowledging an obstacle while affirming action.	〜であっても、〜にもかかわらず。障害を認めつつ動作を肯定する譲歩助詞。	Kahit daghan ang problema, mosugot ko.
30641	30641	but, except, rather. Contrastive or exceptive particle introducing an exception.	しかし、〜を除いて、むしろ。例外や対比を導く逆接・例外助詞。	Wala akoy laing gusto kundi siya.
30642	30642	but, however, nevertheless. Contrastive conjunction introducing opposing or qualifying information.	しかし、けれども、それでも。対立や補足情報を導く逆接接続助詞。	Gusto ko moadto, apan dili ko makahimo.
30643	30643	but, however, yet. Contrastive particle of Spanish origin used widely in Cebuano.	でも、しかし、けれど。セブアノで広く使われるスペイン語由来の逆接助詞。	Gusto ko, pero wala ko kwarta.
30644	30644	that, there near you. Demonstrative particle referring to something near the listener.	あれ、そこの（あなたの近くの）。聞き手の近くにあるものを指す指示助詞。	Unsa man kana ana?
30645	30645	here, come here. Locative or directive particle indicating proximity or invitation.	ここに、こちらへ。近さや招きを示す場所・指示助詞。	Ari, kuha lang.
30646	30646	over there, distant location. Demonstrative particle indicating a location away from both parties.	あそこに、遠くに。話し手・聞き手の双方から離れた場所を示す指示助詞。	Tua siya sa ospital.
30647	30647	intense, very, seriously. Intensifying particle indicating a high or extreme degree.	ひどく、非常に、かなり。高い程度や極端さを示す強調助詞。	Grabi kaayo ang iyang samad.
30648	30648	as said, reportedly. Quotative particle marking reported speech or information.	〜によると、〜だそうで。報告された発言や情報を示す引用助詞。	Sabi niya dili siya makaabot.
30649	30649	really, truly, genuinely. Emphatic affirmation particle asserting genuine truth.	本当に、まさに、確かに。真実であることを強く断言する強調助詞。	Talaga nga mahal nako siya.
30650	30650	I, me (first person singular). First person singular pronoun used as subject or predicate focus.	私、僕（一人称単数）。主語または述語焦点として使われる一人称単数代名詞。	Ako si Maria.
30651	30651	my, mine, by me. Genitive or actor focus form of ako indicating possession or agent.	私の、僕の、私によって。所有または行為者を示すakoの属格・行為者焦点形。	Ang libro nako ania dinhi.
30652	30652	to me, for me, at me. Oblique form of ako used with locative or benefactive meaning.	私に、私のために。場所・受益の意味を持つakoの斜格形。	Ihatag kanako ang papel.
30653	30653	mine, belonging to me. Possessive predicate pronoun asserting that something belongs to the speaker.	私のもの。話し手のものであることを述べる所有述語代名詞。	Akoa kining bag-ong sapatos.
30654	30654	my (ligature form). Linked genitive form of ako used before a noun with the linker -ng.	私の〜（連結形）。連結辞-ngを伴ってakoが名詞の前に置かれる属格連結形。	Akong inahan nagpuyo sa Sugbo.
30655	30655	you (second person singular subject). Second person singular pronoun used primarily in predicate or subject position.	あなた（二人称単数主語）。主語や述語位置で主に使われる二人称単数代名詞。	Ikaw ba ang naghimo niini?
30656	30656	you (enclitic second person singular). Short enclitic form of ikaw placed after the verb or particle.	あなた（後接二人称単数）。動詞や助詞の後に置かれるikawの短縮後接形。	Maayo ka mosinggit.
30657	30657	your, yours, by you. Genitive or actor focus form indicating second person singular possession or agent.	あなたの、あなたによって。二人称単数の所有または行為者を示す属格・行為者焦点形。	Asa ang balay nimo?
30658	30658	to you, for you, at you. Oblique form of ikaw expressing location, direction, or beneficiary.	あなたに、あなたのために。方向・場所・受益を表すikawの斜格形。	Nagpadala siya ug sulat kanimo.
30659	30659	your, yours (possessive predicate). Possessive predicate pronoun indicating something belongs to the second person.	あなたのもの（所有述語）。あるものが二人称のものであることを述べる所有述語代名詞。	Imo ba kining kwarta?
30660	30660	your (ligature form). Linked genitive form of ikaw used before nouns with the linker -ng.	あなたの〜（連結形）。連結辞-ngを伴ってikawが名詞の前に置かれる属格連結形。	Imong amahan nag-abot na.
30661	30661	his, her, its, by him/her. Genitive form of siya indicating third person singular possession or agent.	彼の、彼女の、それの、彼/彼女によって。三人称単数の所有または行為者を示すsiyaの属格形。	Nawala ang pitaka niya.
30662	30662	to him, to her, for him/her. Oblique form of siya expressing direction, location, or beneficiary.	彼に、彼女に、彼/彼女のために。方向・場所・受益を表すsiyaの斜格形。	Gihatag ko ang regalo kaniya.
30663	30663	his, her, its (possessive predicate). Possessive predicate pronoun asserting third person singular ownership.	彼のもの、彼女のもの（所有述語）。三人称単数の所有を述べる所有述語代名詞。	Iya kining bisikleta.
30664	30664	his, her (ligature form). Linked genitive form of siya used before a noun with the linker -ng.	彼の〜、彼女の〜（連結形）。連結辞-ngを伴ってsiyaが名詞の前に置かれる属格連結形。	Iyang iro nagdagan paingon sa kalsada.
30665	30665	we, us (exclusive first person plural). First person plural exclusive pronoun excluding the listener from the group.	私たち（除外複数）。聞き手を含まない一人称複数除外代名詞。	Kami moadto sa merkado ugma.
30666	30666	our, ours, by us (exclusive). Genitive exclusive first person plural indicating possession or agent excluding listener.	私たちの、私たちによって（除外）。聞き手を除く一人称複数の所有または行為者を示す属格除外形。	Ang balay namo bag-o pa.
30667	30667	to us, for us (exclusive). Oblique exclusive first person plural expressing direction or beneficiary excluding listener.	私たちに、私たちのために（除外）。聞き手を除く一人称複数の方向・受益を表す斜格除外形。	Ipadala kanamo ang imbitasyon.
30685	30685	of this; from this. Genitive or locative form of kini, indicating possession or origin.	これの・これから。kini の属格または場所格形で、所有や起点を表す。	Niini ang sugo sa atong ginoo.
30686	30686	of that; from that. Genitive form of kana, referring to something near the listener.	それの・それから。kana の属格形で、聞き手の近くにあるものを指す。	Niana ang among gipangayo.
30687	30687	of this (specific). Emphatic genitive form of kini used before nouns.	このこと・この（特定）。名詞の前で用いる kini の強調属格形。	Niining dapit kay lain ang balaod.
30688	30688	of that (near listener, specific). Emphatic genitive form of kana used before a noun.	そのこと・その（聞き手側、特定）。名詞の前で用いる kana の強調属格形。	Nianang balay ang among gipalit.
30689	30689	of that (far, specific). Emphatic genitive form of kadto used before a specific noun.	あのこと・あの（遠称、特定）。特定の名詞の前で用いる kadto の強調属格形。	Niadtong adlawa hilak ko kaayo.
30690	30690	this (before a noun). Form of kini used directly before a noun it modifies.	この（名詞前置形）。後続する名詞を修飾する kini の連結形。	Kining bataa kusog kaayo mosulti.
30691	30691	go there (near listener). Directional adverb indicating going toward the listener's area.	そこへ行け（聞き手側）。聞き手のいる方向への移動を示す方向副詞。	Panha na mo sa inyong klase.
30692	30692	going there (far, directional). Indicates movement directed toward a distant place.	あそこへ（遠称、方向）。遠くの場所への移動を表す方向副詞。	Padto na siya sa trabaho.
30693	30693	now; at this time. Temporal demonstrative referring to the current moment.	今・現在。現在の時点を指す時間的指示副詞。	Karong adlawa usahon nako ang tanang butang.
30694	30694	this (colloquial linker form). Colloquial contracted form of kining used before nouns.	この（口語連結形）。名詞の前に用いる kining の口語短縮形。	Ining bayhana kaayo ka maayo mosulti.
30695	30695	that (far, colloquial noun linker). Colloquial form of kadtong used before a noun.	あの（遠称、口語名詞連結形）。名詞の前で用いる kadtong の口語形。	Adtong adlawa dili ko malimtan.
30696	30696	here and there; nearby. Compound demonstrative indicating scattered nearby locations.	あちこちに・この辺りに。近くの場所に散在することを示す複合指示副詞。	Dinhi-diha ang iyang mga gamit.
30697	30697	there and beyond; in that area. Compound demonstrative indicating a general far area.	あの辺りに・その先に。遠い一帯の場所を示す複合指示副詞。	Diha-didto ang mga mag-uuma nag-ani.
30698	30698	that one there (near listener, emphatic). Emphatic colloquial variant pointing to something near the listener.	そこにあるそれ（聞き手側、強調）。聞き手の近くにあるものを指す強調口語変異形。	Kara ba ang imong giingon?
30699	30699	who is this/that. Demonstrative interrogative asking for identity of a person.	誰ですか。人物の同一性を尋ねる指示疑問代名詞。	Kinsay tawo didto sa pultahan?
30700	30700	there is/are there (far). Existential demonstrative indicating presence at a distant location.	あそこにある・いる（遠称）。遠くの場所における存在を表す存在指示副詞。	Atua ang mga hayop sa lasang.
30701	30701	here is/are; present here. Existential demonstrative indicating presence at speaker's location.	ここにある・います（近称）。話し手のいる場所における存在を表す存在指示副詞。	Ania na ang imong pagkaon.
30702	30702	now (variant spelling). Alternate orthographic form of karon used in informal writing.	今（異表記）。karon の非公式な異なる綴り形。	Karun na ta molarga.
30703	30703	here and there (widely spread). Compound adverb indicating items scattered over a broad area.	あちこちに（広範囲）。広い範囲に散在することを表す複合副詞。	Dinhi-didto ang mga bangag sa dalan.
30704	30704	this and that; various things. Compound demonstrative indicating miscellaneous nearby items.	あれこれ・いろいろなもの。近くのさまざまなものを示す複合指示代名詞。	Kani-kana ang iyang gihisgotan.
30705	30705	what. Used to ask about the identity or nature of something.	何。物事の正体や性質を尋ねる疑問代名詞。	Unsa ang imong ngalan?
30706	30706	what is (contracted form). Contracted form of 'unsa ang', used in direct questions.	何ですか（縮約形）。「unsa ang」の縮約形で、直接疑問文に用いる。	Unsay imong gusto?
30707	30707	what to do with; how to handle. Asks what action will be taken regarding something.	どうする・どう扱う。あるものに対してどのような処置をとるかを問う動詞。	Unsaon nako ning problema?
30708	30708	what should be done with it. Expresses uncertainty about what to do with a specific thing.	それをどうすればいいのか。特定のものに対して何をすべきか分からないことを表す動詞。	Unsaona man ning mga basura?
30709	30709	who; whom. Used to ask about the identity of a person.	誰・誰を。人物の同一性を尋ねる疑問代名詞。	Kinsa ang nagtawag nako?
30710	30710	whose; who (linker form). Used to link the question word 'kinsa' to a following noun.	誰の・誰（連結形）。後続する名詞に疑問詞 kinsa を結びつける連結形。	Kinsang bag-o ang nagsulti niana?
30711	30711	where. Used to ask about the location or destination of someone or something.	どこ。人や物の場所や目的地を尋ねる疑問副詞。	Asa ka padulong?
30712	30712	where is (contracted form). Contracted form of 'asa ang', used when asking about location.	どこですか（縮約形）。場所を尋ねる「asa ang」の縮約形。	Asay akong bag?
30713	30713	how was it done; how did. Asks about the manner or method by which something was done.	どうやって行われたか・どうした。物事が行われた方法や手段を尋ねる動詞。	Giunsa nimo pagluto ang tinola?
30714	30714	what kind of; which (linker). Linker form of 'unsa', used before a noun to specify type.	どんな種類の・どの（連結形）。後続する名詞の種類を特定する unsa の連結形。	Unsang klase sa trabaho ang gusto nimo?
30715	30715	at, in, on, to (locative marker). Marks location, direction, or time in a sentence.	～で・～に・～へ（場所格助詞）。文中で場所・方向・時間を示す格助詞。	Naa ko sa balay.
30716	30716	for, on behalf of. Marks the beneficiary or purpose of an action.	～のために・～に代わって。行為の受益者や目的を示す助詞。	Kini alang kanimo.
30717	30717	here, toward the speaker. Indicates direction or location near the speaker.	ここへ・話し手の方へ。話し手の近くの方向または場所を示す。	Dali ngari kanamo.
30718	30718	so that; in order to; to. Expresses purpose or intent behind an action.	～するために・～するよう（目的）。行為の目的や意図を表す接続詞。	Nag-aral siya aron makapasar.
30719	30719	even if; even though; although. Colloquial variant of bisan, used in informal speech to show concession.	たとえ～でも・～にもかかわらず。口語的な譲歩を表す接続詞。bisan の口語変異形。	Bisag mahal, palitон nako.
